JOS – The Catholic Laity Council of Nigeria has pleaded with Christian youths in the country not to take the law into their hands but seek vengeance from God Almighty. The National President of the Council Sir Henry Yunkwap while speaking to newsmen in Jos on Monday, condemned the killings of over 50 Christians in Owo, in Ondo state describing it as barbaric and wicked . According to him, as a Christian group and direct mourners of the deceased they do not want to only condemned this babarric act carried out by this animals in human skin but use this medium to let the government know that they have had enough of this killing of their people and now find it very difficult to chew what they forcefully put in out our mouth . -Advertisement- He added that the only option left is to throw it out stressing that for any government who can not provide security for her people, is indirectly telling them to defend themselves by what ever means they can. The President lamented that “We are indeed tired of words , we want actions and the urgent arrest and prosecution of the pepertrators of this heinous act .” “Our leaders must raise against this act instead of just condemning it by using the over used words “We will bring the perpetrators to book.” “They must see the life of every Nigerian as very important not minding where he or she comes from. He added what the victims want from the Government now so that their souls to rest in peace is the assurance that their killers will be arrested and dealt with according to the laws of the land.